
The LogClient can read the OB.log file produced by the
ConceptBase Server, which stores all tell, untell, 
tell_model and ask actions in this log file. 

You need a C compiler to compile this program. Type

	gmake -f MakeLogClient

to compile and link the client.


This program needs at least three command line arguments:
   
   LogClient <portnr> <host> <logfile> [-t] [-a]
   
The -t argument is optional, when it used the client
will wait after each command until you press the return key.
When the -a option is specified, the LogClient will ask
the user, if a command should be executed.

Remember that it is not a good idea, to use the log file
of a running server and to connect to that server. This
will be an endless loop.

This is also a small example for the usage of the 
ConceptBase programming interface (libCB).

--
Remark: Since 9-Oct-2006, the ConceptBase server no longer writes into
the log file OB.log. Therefore, the LogClient is now an obsolete
utility. M. Jeusfeld, 9_Oct-2006

